Wracked by insomnia and wanderlust, Kou Yamori is driven onto the moonlit streets every night in an aimless search for something he can’t seem to name. His nightly ritual is marked by purposeless introspection — until he meets Nazuna, who might just be a vampire! Kou’s new companion could offer him dark gifts and a vampire’s immortality. But there are conditions that must be met before Kou can sink his teeth into vampirism, and he’ll have to discover just how far he’s willing to go to satisfy his desires before he can heed the Call of the Night!
(Source: Sentai Filmworks)

How can you fall in love when you can’t even hold hands? Due to a childhood curse, anything that the Duke touches will die—which makes his flirty maid’s behavior all the more shocking! Is there a way for the Duke and his companions to somehow break the curse, or is he doomed to a life where love is forever out of his reach?
(Source: Funimation)
Me ga Sametara Tougoku sareta Akujo datta @COMIC

Sophia, an apothecary who has been abused by the "Shameless Countess," wakes up one day to find herself in a prison cell. She has taken over the body of the bewitching beauty Violet, and the only clue she has is a note that says, "Please protect my body." Sophia is at a loss at first, but life in prison turns out to be more enjoyable than she expected! Meanwhile, Violet wakes up in Sophia's body, and starts working toward her goal, while showing off her new "arrogant bad-girl" attitude... This is a fantastical story of double revenge for a lady apothecary and a rare villainess, starting from opposite sides of the same coin!

(Source: Corona EX, translated)

When Ji-Yong Kim was a boy, his mother was murdered. The assailant was tried in the court of law but served a mere three and a half years because he “deeply regrets his actions.” 17 years later, Ji-Yong is a college student, studying to become a police officer. But on the weekends, Ji-Yong hunts down ex-convicts released by a justice system that has failed to protect the victims, taking justice into his own hands to make up for its shortcomings.
(Source: WEBTOONS, edited)
